sc_cat_item_producer.description:
1. To Submit Alert and Recall WO Creation or Reassign Request
    If you are requesting the creation of alert WOs you must include Equip IDs (not CEIDs) and the alert code ALT000XXX if the alert has been addressed by the Regulatory Department. If not addressed, submit the alert and recall document under the Alert and Recall Documentation Submission section.If you are requesting the reassignment of alert WOs include the WO number(s), current technician assignment, and who the WO should be reassigned to.
  2. To Submit Alert and Recall Document Submission Request
    Attach the alert documentation along with an excel spreadsheet of affected devices, including the Equip IDs (not CEIDs).
  3. To Submit Alert and Recall Bulk WO Update Request
    Please provide the alert code (ALT000XXX) and attach an excel spreadsheet of alert WOs that need to be updated. 
    Include the following fields from RSQ:
    • Work Order Number
    • CEID, SN, Mfr, Model Name, Model Number
    • Reported Problem (this contains the ALT000XXX code)
  4. To Submit a Bulk Close Request for Not Affected WOs
    If you are requesting a bulk close for alert WOs, this is only applicable for WOs with an Action Code of Investigated and a Follow Up Code of Not Affected. The request must include a note for the reason as to why the alert was not affected. On top of that, you need toinclude the name of the technician to be entered into the labor line, and the time per WO (must be greater than 5 mins). The WOs can be in a 10E or 60A status. 
  5. To Submit Alert and Recall General/Others Questions
